snippet.textDisplay: This is an almost word-for-word reprise of the same sketch ("You're married to her? Really?  No F'in Way! Can't be! Etc.ETC!" ) that they did, LAST season, with Margot Robbie (and they even used the same actor as the geek husband no less).  But over-all they wasted J-Lo on a third-rate D+ episode with not one funny moment in it.  (Compare it with the Chance the Rapper episode, from Halloween, that was pretty great and had lots of good sketches).  After one too many (and one really is too many) of the "NEWS" segments with Che and Jost, and their tedious, caustically sarcastic and bitter rants I just FF through all that every single ep... now, I'm a long time fan of SNL, seen almost every episode ever, and I do grasp that not ALL the SNL episodes can be gems!  The creative demands of the show are no doubt massive, and in any long term creative endeavor like SNL, constant perfection and comedic genius, is an impossibility!  So there are going to be clinker sketches and whole episodes that just don't seem to work.  But nowadays every time I watch a new SNL episodes, i'm half-expecting a D grade episode - like this one.  Let's face it, this wasn't their best work and just makes me wonder if SNL has a future, when Lorne Michaels is no longer involved in the show (and what a sad day that will be).  I suspect that S.N.L. will end when Michaels departs - and perhaps that is exactly how it ought to end.
